<p>
<H3>Fig. 3</H3>  
<p>
  A plot of the differences between each baffled profile and the vertical polarity unbaffled profile (lower means more attenuation). Clearly the scaled down baffle has the most consistent performance. Interestingly, all perform poorly at angles >60 deg. We know that reflections dominate around 80deg, but somehow all of the baffles have higher response ~10 deg on either side.
<p>
